OL,3,CThousands gather in Oxford for annual
OL,4,CMay Morning celebrations
OL,6,FTraditional events and activities,
OL,7,Fincluding Morris Dancing and folk
OL,8,Fsinging, took place across the city as
OL,9,Fthe bell of the Great Tower rang out.
OL,11,FPaula Redway, Oxford City Council's
OL,12,FCulture and Community Development
OL,13,FManager, called it a "wonderful
OL,14,Fmorning".
OL,16,FShe said: "With roots stretching back
OL,17,Fmore than 500 years, May Morning
OL,18,Fremains one of Oxford's most treasured
OL,19,Ftraditions - seeing so many people
OL,20,Freturn year after year really shows
OL,21,Fhow special it is."
OL,1,W~s1x0~s1~s hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}   G3/4
